For every round that has PRIMARY CHANNEL messages, return one entry in ``per_round`` with:

1. ``round_number`` — the round.
2. ``distinct_units`` — how many DISTINCT pieces of information the agents conveyed on the PRIMARY CHANNEL this round. Count each value/instruction/field once: a motif name, a face, an intensity, a duration, a count, a confirmation, etc.
3. ``total_encodings`` — the total number of times those units were transmitted, counting EVERY copy and EVERY alternate form of the same unit. A unit stated once adds 1; "12 12" adds 2 for that unit; "T1 T1 T1" adds 3; "12 twelve" adds 2 (digit + word form of one value); "gnt gentle" adds 2 (abbreviation + full word). ``total_encodings`` is always >= ``distinct_units``.
4. ``examples`` — the most-repeated units with their multiplicity, e.g. "T1 x3", "12/twelve x2", "gnt/gentle x2" (empty list if nothing was repeated).

We compute a redundancy factor = total_encodings / distinct_units per round (1.0 = everything said once, 2.0 = everything said twice on average, 3.0 = three times). Count consistently so these factors are comparable across rounds. Skip rounds with no PRIMARY CHANNEL messages.

